      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Acceptance Criteria\n\n- User can choose Local without seeing GitHub controls.\n- User can choose GitHub and then see repo/path details.\n- GitHub Work / Private / Public are no longer primary top-level choices.\n- Current graph home is displayed in plain language.\n- Button labels describe user intent, not storage mechanics.\n- Advanced GitHub details are collapsed by default.\n- Save confirmation clearly says where future changes will go.\n- Existing local and GitHub save mechanisms continue to work.\n- UI leaves room for future Twilite Cloud destination.",
        "memo": "",
        "link": "",
        "html": "",
        "svg": "",
