          }
        }
      ],
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "title": "Revised save workflow (intent-first)",
        "body": "Goal: Make saving feel like choosing a home for the graph, not configuring storage.\n\nScope:\n1. Save Graph modal step 1: choose home (Local / GitHub / Cloud-future)\n2. GitHub-only step 2: repo + path (+ advanced collapsed)\n3. Separate \"Set as home\" vs \"Export / Save As\"\n4. Ensure declaration exists before save (not required to edit)\n5. Prevent accidental overwrites (explicit path + confirmation)\n\nStatus: todo",
        "status": "todo",
        "owner": "Michael",
        "priority": "high",
        "estimateHours": "2",
        "acceptanceCriteria": [
          "User can save locally without GitHub controls",
          "GitHub save shows repo/path only after choosing GitHub",
          "Home vs Export is explicit and safe"
        ],
        "countAsTask": false,
        "summarySource": "manual",
        "definitionKey": "task",
